Fusion Trade Innovation

Database changes 2.10.1.3

ACCOUNT - Account

Details of Accounts held by the bank relating to either :-
- Customer accounts - current accounts, liability accounts, loan accounts etc
- Charge income accounts - accounts for recording charge profit and loss e.g. PT - Postage
- Internal accounts-accounts for contra liability, interest and charge accrual, suspense accounts, FX position accounts e.g. SP501 - LC issued contra

Customer accounts are identified by
- branch
- customer mnemonic
- account type
- currency
- sequence number
e.g. LOND ABC RA USD 1

Charge and Internal accounts are identified by
- branch
- category code
- account type
- currency
e.g. LOND 897001 YP USD 1

The category code is essentially a General ledger category used to identify where the account belongs in the bank's general ledger.This category code is used to link TI's System parameters and Charge code to their associated accounts

CAPF - Branch

The branches defined by the bank.

Branches are either transaction branches(where transactions are recorded or business branches (used to structure the bank's banking organisation)

Key attributes are
- banking group - a group of banking businesses/groups
- banking business - a logically separate group of branches representing a particular part of the bank's business
- main banking entity - the G/L that covers a number of transaction branches and their accounts. Base currency is defined at this level.
[pre]
[ Banking business/group ]
MBWW
/ \
Main banking entity -> [MBUK] [MBUS]
/ | \ / | \
Branches B1 B2 B3 B4 B5 B6
[/pre]

  • p = Both dates on previous working day, keep in same month
  • O = Due date only on next working day
  • o = Due date only on next working day, keep in same month
  • Q = Due date only on previous working day
  • q = Due date only on previous working day, keep in same month

MASTER - Master

The basic details for any Product Master from which all Products such as Letter of credits, Guarantees, Collections ,Finance deals etc are derived.

The master holds common details such as :-
- Amount
- Current liability
- Expiry date
- References
- Principal/Non principal parties
- Master status - LIV, EXP, CAN , BKF
- User codes

When events are completed the master details and associated data (TI data items) are updated so that the master represents the current state.

  • M = Invoice settlement date outside of maximum period
  • m = Forced eligible (Invoice settlement date outside of maximum period)
  • N = Invoice status is dishonoured
  • n = Forced eligible (Invoice status is dishonoured)
  • O = Invoice status is cancelled
  • o = Forced eligible (Invoice status is cancelled)
  • P = Invoice status is under inquiry
  • p = Forced eligible (Invoice status is under inquiry)
  • Q = Invoice status is paid
  • q = Forced eligible (Invoice status is paid)
  • R = Invoice has referred buyer
  • r = Forced eligible (Invoice has referred buyer)
  • S = Invoice is being financed
  • T = Invoice requires approval
  • t = Forced eligible (Invoice requires approval)
  • U = Invoice has blocked seller
  • u = Forced eligible (Invoice has blocked seller)
  • V = Invoice has referred seller
  • v = Forced eligible (Invoice has referred seller)
  • W = Invoice has invalid received on date
  • w = Forced eligible (Invoice has invalid received on date)
  • X = Invoice programme or seller buyer limits fully utilised
  • x = Forced eligible (Invoice programme or seller buyer limits fully utilised)
  • Y = Invoice is already financed
  • Z = Invoice is booked off
  • 0 = Gateway transaction refused
 string(1) EligibilityReason

  • I = Force ineligible for drawdown
